parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of defective brake pads and rotors can lead to premature wear, grinding, and damage to other brake components, resulting in reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
Sudden brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
Unintended acceleration and brake failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: failure to stop when brakes are applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the driver or passenger to become stuck in the seat belt, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is inoperative
the seat belt buckle won't detach
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the plastic cover on the passenger's side buckle has fallen off
the seat belts do not retract when not in use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle fails to respond to braking inputs.
symptoms: The engine races or surges without the driver's input
the vehicle accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle maintains a constant speed despite attempts to slow down
the brakes are ineffective in stopping the vehicle.
